•  Manual configuration
•  Use the cluster-admin role only when required.
Profile Applicability: 
•  Level 2
Description: 
The cluster-admin role is a more restricted role than the cluster-admin role. 
It provides access to only certain resources and permissions, 
limiting its use to tasks that are critical to the cluster's security. 
Rationale: 
The cluster-admin role is designed to provide a secure and reliable foundation for 
Kubernetes clusters. It allows administrators to manage and secure the 
cluster's infrastructure. 
Impact: 
Care should be taken before removing any clusterrolebindings from the environment
