Amazon ECR Identity-Based Policies 
With IAM identity-based policies, you can specify allowed or denied actions and 
resources as well as the conditions under which actions are allowed or denied. Amazon 
ECR supports specific actions, resources, and condition keys. To learn about all of the 
elements that you use in a JSON policy, see IAM JSON Policy Elements Reference in 
the IAM User Guide. 
Actions 
The Action element of an IAM identity-based policy describes the specific action or 
actions that will be allowed or denied by the policy. Policy actions usually have the 
same
...
zero_shot_prompt
...
name as the policy. 
For example, "Allow" action allows the specified action, while "Deny" 
action denies the specified action. 
Conditions 
The Condition element of an IAM identity-based policy specifies the conditions 
under which the action is allowed or denied. Conditions can be based on 
various attributes of the resources being accessed. 
For example, "ResourceTag" condition checks if the resource 
has a specific tag. 
The condition can be a string, a number, or a boolean. 
For example, "ResourceTag" condition checks if the resource 
has a specific tag. 
The condition can be a string, a number, or a boolean.
